<tr>
<td><i>Lo breviari d'amors</i></td>
<td>"Breviary of love"</td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Matfre_Ermengau" title="Matfre Ermengau">Matfre Ermengau</a></td>
<td>begun 1288</td>
<td>
<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/File:Ensenhamen.PNG" class="image" title="Ensenhamen.PNG"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/8d/Ensenhamen.PNG/75px-Ensenhamen.PNG" width="75" height="144" border="0" /></a></div>
A pious <a href="/wiki/Encyclopedia" title="Encyclopedia">encyclopedia</a>, the last section of which, "Perilhos tractatz d'amor de donas, seguon qu'en han tractat li antic trobador en lurs cansos", is an Occitan grammar.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>Doctrina d'acort</i><sup id="cite_ref-23" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-23" title=""><span>[</span>24<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
<td>"Doctrinal of concordance"</td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Terramagnino_da_Pisa" title="Terramagnino da Pisa">Terramagnino da Pisa</a></td>
<td>1282–96, Sardinia</td>
<td>A condensed verse adaptation of the <i>Razos</i>, poorly preserved in the manuscripts.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>Regles de trobar</i><sup id="cite_ref-24" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-24" title=""><span>[</span>25<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
<td>"Rules of composition"</td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Jaufre_de_Foixa" title="Jaufre de Foixa" class="mw-redirect">Jaufre de Foixa</a></td>
<td>1289–91, Sicily</td>
<td>
<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/File:Regles_de_Trobar.jpg" class="image" title="Regles de Trobar.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/63/Regles_de_Trobar.jpg/75px-Regles_de_Trobar.jpg" width="75" height="97" border="0" /></a></div>
