<td>"Laws of love"</td>
<td><a href="/w/index.php?title=Guilhem_Molinier&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Guilhem Molinier (page does not exist)">Guilhem Molinier</a></td>
<td>1328–37, Toulouse</td>
<td>
<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/File:Leys_d%27amor,_initial.jpg" class="image" title="Leys d'amor, initial.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/47/Leys_d%27amor%2C_initial.jpg/75px-Leys_d%27amor%2C_initial.jpg" width="75" height="99" border="0" /></a></div>
First commissioned in 1323. Prose rules governing the <a href="/wiki/Consistori_del_Gay_Saber" title="Consistori del Gay Saber">Consistori del Gay Saber</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Consistori_de_Barcelona" title="Consistori de Barcelona">Consistori de Barcelona</a>.</td>
